.TH SORT_SCHEMA 1 
.SH NAME
sort_schema - sort attributes and relations aplhabetically.
Usefile when cleaning up databases schemata and extension tables.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
sort_schema schemafile sorted_schema
.fi

.SH DESCRIPTION
sort_schema sorts the contents of an input database schema or table definition.
Firts, all attribute definitions are listed in alphabetical orer, then all relations.
.SH OPTIONS
.IP "sechemafile"
filename of the input schema or table definition. This argument is required.

.IP "sorted_schema"
Output filename. This argument is required.

.SH EXAMPLE
.nf
sort_schema css3.0 /tmp/testfile
.fi

.SH "BUGS AND CAVEATS"
Flawless if the input schema is correct.
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.nf
dbschema(5), dbe(1), check_schema(1), schema2tables(1) 
.fi
